@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy for IT Tools for Developers";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="container">
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> April 30, 2025</p>
    <p>Welcome to IT Tools for Developers ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our software application, which provides tools to support developers, as outlined in the TKPM - Project #2 documentation. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring transparency in our data practices.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect the following types of information to provide and improve our services:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Anonymous Users:</strong> For users accessing the platform without an account, we may collect non-personal information such as usage data (e.g., which tools are used, frequency of use) and technical data (e.g., browser type, IP address, device information) to analyze trends and improve functionality.</li>
        <li>
            <strong>Registered Users (User and Premium Accounts):</strong> When you register or upgrade to a premium account, we collect personal information including:
            <ul>
                <li>Email address (for account creation and communication).</li>
                <li>Username or display name (to personalize your experience).</li>
                <li>Password (stored securely using industry-standard encryption).</li>
                <li>Optional preferences, such as favorited tools or settings for personalized dashboards.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Admin Users:</strong> For admin accounts, we collect additional information related to administrative actions, such as tool management logs, to ensure system integrity and accountability.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We collect data on how you interact with our tools (e.g., generating tokens, converting JSON to XML, creating QR codes) to enhance user experience and optimize performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies:</strong> We use cookies and similar technologies to track user preferences, session management, and analytics. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Delivery:</strong> To provide access to tools, manage user accounts, and enable features like favoriting tools or premium tool access.</li>
        <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> To customize your experience, such as displaying your favorite tools on a dedicated dashboard for registered users.</li>
        <li><strong>System Administration:</strong> For admins, to manage tools (enable/disable, upgrade/downgrade, add/remove) and ensure system functionality.</li>
        <li><strong>Improvement and Analytics:</strong> To analyze usage patterns, identify popular tools, and enhance the platform's performance and user interface.</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To send account-related notifications (e.g., password reset emails, premium upgrade confirmations) and, if you opt-in, promotional updates about new tools or features.</li>
        <li><strong>Security:</strong> To protect against unauthorized access, detect and prevent fraud, and ensure the integrity of our platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> With trusted third-party providers who assist with hosting, analytics, or payment processing (for premium accounts). These providers are contractually obligated to protect your data and use it only for the services they provide to us.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> If required by law, regulation, or legal process (e.g., court order, subpoena), we may disclose your information to comply with such obligations.</li>
        <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the acquiring entity, with continued protection under this policy or a similar standard.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information, including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Encryption of sensitive data (e.g., passwords, payment information) during transmission and storage.</li>
        <li>Access controls to limit data access to authorized personnel only.</li>
        <li>Regular security audits and updates to address vulnerabilities.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>While we strive to protect your data, no system is completely secure. Please use strong passwords and avoid sharing your account credentials.</p>

    <h2>5. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your account and associated data, subject to legal retention requirements.</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Opt out of promotional communications at any time via the unsubscribe link in emails or your account settings.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Manage cookie preferences through your browser or our cookie consent tool (if applicable).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at [insert contact email]. We will respond within a reasonable timeframe, typically within 30 days, as required by applicable laws.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services. For example:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Anonymous usage data is retained for up to 12 months for analytics purposes.</li>
        <li>Registered user data is retained until you request deletion or your account becomes inactive for 24 months, after which it is securely deleted.</li>
        <li>Admin logs are retained for 36 months to ensure system accountability.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We may retain certain data longer if required by law or for legitimate business purposes (e.g., resolving disputes).</p>

    <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our platform is not intended for users under 13 years of age (or 16 in certain jurisdictions). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that a child has provided personal information, we will take steps to delete it promptly.</p>

    <h2>8. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>Our servers and service providers may be located in jurisdictions outside your country. We ensure that any international data transfers comply with applicable data protection laws, such as using standard contractual clauses or relying on adequacy decisions.</p>

    <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>Our platform may include links to third-party websites (e.g., <a href="https://it-tools.tech/" target="_blank">https://it-tools.tech/</a>). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these websites. Please review their privacy policies before providing personal information.</p>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify registered users of significant changes via email or a prominent notice on the platform. The updated policy will be effective as of the date posted.</p>

